  "text": "## Prometheus Alertmanager Notification Pipeline in Grafana Mimir\n\nThe alertmanager notification pipeline in Grafana Mimir (using prometheus/alertmanager) follows this flow:\n\n### 1. Alert Ingestion\n**Entry Point**: `vendor/github.com/prometheus/alertmanager/api/v2/api.go::postAlertsHandler`\n- HTTP POST handler at `/api/v2/alerts` receives incoming alerts\n- Converts PostableAlerts to internal Alert types with validation\n- Calls `api.alerts.Put()` to store alerts in the provider\n\n### 2. Alert Storage Provider\n**File**: `vendor/github.com/prometheus/alertmanager/provider/mem/alerts.go`\n- In-memory alert storage that implements the `provider.Alerts` interface\n- Stores alerts and notifies subscribers through channels\n- Dispatcher subscribes to receive alert updates\n\n### 3. Dispatcher and Alert Processing\n**File**: `vendor/github.com/prometheus/alertmanager/dispatch/dispatch.go`\n- `Dispatcher` class is the core alert processing component\n- `Run()` method starts the dispatcher, subscribing to alert updates\n- Receives alerts from the provider and processes them sequentially\n- For each alert, extracts group labels and creates/updates aggregation groups\n\n### 4. Routing Tree Traversal\n**File**: `vendor/github.com/prometheus/alertmanager/dispatch/route.go`\n- `Route` class implements the routing tree\n- `Route.Match(alert.Labels)` performs depth-first, left-to-right search through routing tree\n- Returns all matching routes for an alert based on label matchers\n- Respects the `Continue` flag to determine if sibling routes should be evaluated\n\n### 5. Notification Pipeline Stages\n**File**: `vendor/github.com/prometheus/alertmanager/notify/notify.go`\n- Pipeline executes as a series of stages: `Stage` interface\n- Each stage can modify alerts or context before passing to next stage\n- Pipeline order in `GrafanaAlertmanager.ApplyConfig()` (line 745):\n  1. GossipSettleStage (mesh settling)\n  2. SilencingStage (silence check)\n  3. TimeActiveStage (time interval active check)\n  4. TimeMuteStage (mute time interval check)\n  5. InhibitionStage (inhibition check)\n  6. RoutingStage (route-specific receivers)\n  7. Integration-specific stages (dedup, retry, notification logging)\n\n### 6. Silence Check\n**File**: `vendor/github.com/prometheus/alertmanager/silence/silence.go`\n- `Silencer` class implements the `Muter` interface\n- Bound to `silence.Silences` which stores silence rules\n- `Mutes(ctx, alerts)` checks if alerts match any active silence matchers\n- Wrapped in `MuteStage` in the notification pipeline\n\n### 7. Inhibition Check\n**File**: `vendor/github.com/prometheus/alertmanager/inhibit/inhibit.go`\n- `Inhibitor` class implements the `Muter` interface\n- Evaluates inhibition rules against active alerts\n- `Mutes(ctx, alerts)` returns true if an alert should be inhibited\n- Wrapped in `MuteStage` in the notification pipeline\n- Inhibition rules define which alerts suppress other alerts based on labels\n\n### 8. Notifier Dispatch and Integration\n**File**: `vendor/github.com/grafana/alerting/notify/grafana_alertmanager.go`\n- `GrafanaAlertmanager` wrapper provides integration management\n- `ApplyConfig()` method (line 715) constructs the notification pipeline:\n  - Creates `RoutingStage` (map of receiver names to their stage pipelines)\n  - For each receiver, creates `FanoutStage` with integration-specific stages\n- `createReceiverStage()` (line 910) builds the final integration stages:\n  - WaitStage (cluster peer coordination)\n  - DedupStage (deduplication based on notification log)\n  - RetryStage (retry logic for failed notifications)\n  - SetNotifiesStage (records notification in notification log)\n  - All wrapped in FanoutStage to execute integrations concurrently\n\n### 9. Mimir Alertmanager Wrapper\n**File**: `pkg/alertmanager/alertmanager.go`\n- `Alertmanager` class wraps alertmanager components for single tenant\n- Manages configuration application, state persistence, and replication\n- Registers HTTP API endpoints for alert management\n- Integrates with Mimir's multi-tenancy and cluster coordination\n\n### Complete Flow Summary\n1. Alert arrives at `postAlertsHandler` (api/v2/api.go)\n2. Alert stored in `Alerts` provider (provider/mem/alerts.go)\n3. Dispatcher notified of new alert (dispatch/dispatch.go)\n4. Alert labels matched against routing tree (dispatch/route.go::Match)\n5. For each matching route, create aggregation group\n6. Aggregated alerts flow through pipeline stages:\n   - Silence check (silence/silence.go::Silencer)\n   - Inhibition check (inhibit/inhibit.go::Inhibitor)\n   - Route-specific receiver selection (notify/notify.go::RoutingStage)\n   - Integration-specific processing (notify/notify.go::FanoutStage)\n7. Final notifier dispatch to external receivers (Slack, PagerDuty, etc.)\n8. Notification recorded in notification log (nflog)\n"
}

